+### Sequence number {#sequence-number}
+
+Swan assigns a `sequenceNumber` to every `Booked` transaction.
+The number increments by 1 with each new booked transaction per account, providing a reliable way to order transactions and detect gaps.
+
+`sequenceNumber` is also used to order `Booked` transactions on the [account statement](../accounts/index.mdx#account-statements).
+
+`sequenceNumber` is available in `BookedTransactionStatusInfo.balanceAfter` when you [query](https://explorer.swan.io/?%3D%3D&tab=api) `statusInfo`.
+
+`sequenceNumber` returns `null` for all transaction statuses other than `Booked`.
+
 ### Transaction supporting documents {#transactions-supporting-documents}
 
 In certain cases, Swan requires supporting documents to justify transactions.
